1
00:00:33,480 --> 00:00:35,160
Where is the USB drive and how do I get it?

2
00:00:35,160 --> 00:00:38,680
Tomorrow, this USB drive will be sent from the airport to another location.

3
00:00:38,680 --> 00:00:40,880
I will give you the relevant information later.

4
00:00:40,880 --> 00:00:42,740
And someone will assist you then.

5
00:00:48,440 --> 00:00:51,120
It seems you know more than I thought.

6
00:00:52,360 --> 00:00:54,280
So you must be quite familiar with this USB drive.

7
00:00:54,280 --> 00:00:55,080
Of course.

8
00:00:55,760 --> 00:00:56,880
Tomorrow's mission

9
00:00:56,880 --> 00:00:57,940
was arranged by me.

10
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:02,640
I have a client

11
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:05,280
who has some confidential data to store,

12
00:01:05,280 --> 00:01:07,920
so they hired a computer expert named Jessica,

13
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:10,080
the girl you rescued.

14
00:01:11,120 --> 00:01:13,450
She designed an encryption system for us.

15
00:01:13,720 --> 00:01:15,039
Through this system,

16
00:01:15,360 --> 00:01:17,640
the data is stored in two USB drives.

17
00:01:17,640 --> 00:01:19,360
One is with my client,

18
00:01:19,800 --> 00:01:21,240
and the other serves as a backup

19
00:01:21,240 --> 00:01:23,300
and is kept in a vault in Switzerland.

20
00:01:23,640 --> 00:01:26,280
There are two ways to access the USB drive.

21
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:29,280
One is the electronic key my client carries with them.

22
00:01:29,280 --> 00:01:30,200
The other

23
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:32,600
is the designer of the encryption system,

24
00:01:32,600 --> 00:01:33,360
Jessica.

25
00:01:34,039 --> 00:01:36,920
She can bypass the electronic key and access it directly.

26
00:01:36,920 --> 00:01:38,720
Once Jessica was rescued by you,

27
00:01:38,880 --> 00:01:39,960
it meant

28
00:01:39,960 --> 00:01:43,090
the backup USB drive stored overseas was no longer safe.

29
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:45,640
So that USB drive must be destroyed.

30
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:50,200
Because of the USB drive's material, it cannot be physically destroyed.

31
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:53,060
So destroying it also requires the electronic key.

32
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:55,360
Hence tomorrow's plan.

33
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:57,800
You want me to steal the USB drive.

34
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:03,240
Tomorrow, this USB drive will arrive at the airport from Switzerland.

35
00:02:03,240 --> 00:02:04,970
And your opportunity to strike

36
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:07,240
is on the way from the airport to the client's company.

37
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:08,120
And then?

38
00:02:08,160 --> 00:02:09,759
In some ways,

39
00:02:09,759 --> 00:02:11,240
our goals align.

40
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:14,200
I want to find the people causing us trouble behind the scenes.

41
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:14,920
And you

42
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,530
want to save your daughter.

43
00:02:17,079 --> 00:02:17,960
So...

44
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:20,040
What do you need me to do?

45
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:23,320
When the USB drive arrives tomorrow,

46
00:02:23,320 --> 00:02:24,640
there will be a tracker on it.

47
00:02:24,640 --> 00:02:25,720
Once you get it,

48
00:02:25,720 --> 00:02:27,240
you and my men will follow the tracker

49
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:28,360
to find them,

50
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:29,640
and

51
00:02:29,640 --> 00:02:30,770
save your daughter.

52
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:34,280
But to make the whole thing more convincing,

53
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:36,800
we won't let you get the USB drive that easily.

54
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:38,200
You'll have to show some real skills.

55
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:40,680
Using such an important USB drive as bait,

56
00:02:41,079 --> 00:02:42,560
isn't it a bit dangerous?

57
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:43,560
We have no choice.

58
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:46,800
If we want to solve the problem once and for all,

59
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:49,120
how can we not pay a price?

60
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:54,160
All right.

61
00:02:55,240 --> 00:02:56,900
I agree to cooperate with you.

62
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:05,890
Pleasure working with you.

63
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:01,880
Hello.

64
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:05,480
Help me look into someone named Li Xiangyou.

65
00:04:05,480 --> 00:04:07,840
See if he has any recent activities.

66
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:52,200
Turn right.

67
00:05:13,440 --> 00:05:14,100
Turn right.

68
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:36,650
Take another route.

69
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:04,480
I found it.

70
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:07,000
They're on the same flight today.

71
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,040
Okay, got it.

72
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:12,680
I have a situation here.

73
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:15,040
They have two routes for escorting the goods today.

74
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:15,800
I previously

75
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:19,160
looked up the person escorting the flash drive. His name is Li Xiangzuo.

76
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:21,360
But because I dealt with their security company before,

77
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:23,000
I know he has a twin brother

78
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,060
named Li Xiangyou.

79
00:06:24,560 --> 00:06:26,320
They usually go on missions together.

80
00:06:26,320 --> 00:06:28,040
But today only Li Xiangzuo is here.

81
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:29,200
So I sent someone to investigate

82
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:30,120
this Li Xiangyou.

83
00:06:30,120 --> 00:06:32,320
Sure enough, they are on the same plane.

84
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:35,600
So the real flash drive should be with Li Xiangyou.

85
00:06:35,920 --> 00:06:37,240
You should send someone over right away.

86
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:39,280
You're only calling me now?

87
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:41,780
Did you think I didn't know anything?

88
00:06:49,880 --> 00:06:50,480
Hello.

89
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:52,720
Help me look up a guy named Li Xiangyou.

90
00:06:52,720 --> 00:06:54,560
See what he's been up to lately.

91
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:57,920
That car behind you is tailing you pretty closely.

92
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:04,680
This is your mission.

93
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:06,080
If you fail,

94
00:07:06,520 --> 00:07:08,200
you know the consequences.

95
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:11,000
I did contact a woman named An Ning before.

96
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:13,520
But I only pretended to cooperate with her to complete the mission.

97
00:07:13,520 --> 00:07:14,960
My original plan was

98
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:16,960
to ditch her once I got the item

99
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,260
and hand it over to you.

100
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:21,000
But I didn't expect to just be her pawn.

101
00:07:21,440 --> 00:07:22,800
This woman has quite a few backup plans.

102
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:25,200
I don't care how many pawns and backup plans she has.

103
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:27,000
I just want the results I asked for.

104
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:29,200
One of them must be real and the other fake.

105
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:30,680
You make the decision yourself.

106
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:32,200
But I don't have the flash drive right now.

107
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:34,840
I can't be sure this lead is fake either.

108
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,200
If you don't want to make a move,

109
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:37,280
there's nothing I can do.

110
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:38,640
Do you actually want to get the item,

111
00:07:38,640 --> 00:07:40,440
or do you just want to see me fail?

112
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:42,080
It's up to you.

113
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:10,200
Turn left.

114
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:29,000
Watch out.

115
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:44,280
Don't open the window yet.

116
00:09:44,280 --> 00:09:45,160
If the paint gets in the car,

117
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:46,420
it'll be hard to clean.

118
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:52,050
Let's get out and check.

119
00:09:58,120 --> 00:09:58,760
Zuo.

120
00:09:58,760 --> 00:09:59,800
We can't drive our car anymore.

121
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:01,200
I'll go find another car.

122
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:02,240
Our car broke down.

123
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:03,320
Can we borrow your car?

124
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:03,840
Sure.

125
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:04,560
Thanks.

126
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:10,960
Zuo.

127
00:10:14,160 --> 00:10:14,720
Zuo.

128
00:10:15,080 --> 00:10:16,840
The company noticed an unexpected situation.

129
00:10:16,840 --> 00:10:17,960
They suspect you're being targeted.

130
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:18,800
Surveillance.

131
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:20,480
We just reported the situation to the company.

132
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:21,400
If there's a problem,

133
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:23,130
why didn't we get any feedback?

134
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:23,800
Also,

135
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:24,800
where is Xiao Wang?

136
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:25,880
Why is he missing?

137
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:28,120
That's why the company sent me here urgently to back you up.

138
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:29,960
I told Xiao Wang to find some tools to fix the car.

139
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:30,400
Listen.

140
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:31,840
You come with me alone now.

141
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:33,680
You two wait for Xiao Wang to come back.

142
00:10:33,680 --> 00:10:34,680
Then get the tools,

143
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:35,440
fix the car,

144
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:37,080
and pretend to deliver the goods as a cover.

145
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:37,560
Understand?

146
00:10:37,560 --> 00:10:38,640
That's against the rules.

147
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:39,320
Special circumstances require special measures.

148
00:10:39,320 --> 00:10:40,120
We can't hesitate anymore.

149
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:43,050
It'll be too late if something happens, Brother Zuo.

150
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:15,080
He got it.

151
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:21,640
Brother You.

152
00:11:21,640 --> 00:11:22,900
I'll go down and check.

153
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:32,250
What's going on?

154
00:11:32,280 --> 00:11:33,010
Brother You.

155
00:11:33,160 --> 00:11:34,360
All four tires are blown.

156
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:36,490
Looks like someone is messing with us.

157
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:38,480
The situation is a bit dangerous now.

158
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:38,960
Xiao Liu,

159
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:39,690
come with me.

160
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:42,320
Fix the car.

161
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:43,440
Then keep posing as deliverymen.

162
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:43,840
Okay.

163
00:11:47,960 --> 00:11:48,240
Driver.

164
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:49,170
To Shifang Road.

165
00:11:59,360 --> 00:11:59,920
Driver.

166
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:01,240
Why stop here?

167
00:12:01,640 --> 00:12:02,900
You went the wrong way.

168
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:14,040
The second box was snatched.
